whether you like it or not.

01:22:48.361 --> 01:22:53.291
And how, exactly, does Little Miss Alabama
plan to accommodate 500 people?

01:22:53.366 --> 01:22:55.357
I suppose she has connections
at the jail.

01:22:55.434 --> 01:22:57.095
Well, there are
several excellent choices...

01:22:57.170 --> 01:23:00.606
the Travelodge,
Days Inn, a Motel 6,...

01:23:00.673 --> 01:23:03.772
oh, and the Golden Cherry Motel,
where we will be.

01:23:03.909 --> 01:23:06.104
Laugh now,
but if this gets out...

01:23:06.178 --> 01:23:07.145
It won't.

01:23:07.212 --> 01:23:10.079
The press expects
the Plaza in June.

01:23:31.869 --> 01:23:33.461
Now, let's talk
about your wedding.

01:23:33.537 --> 01:23:37.495
This place is gorgeous and
we can control the security.

01:23:37.608 --> 01:23:39.098
The Carmichael plantation?

01:23:39.176 --> 01:23:42.043
It did inspire your identity,
did it not?

01:23:42.112 --> 01:23:44.272
You thought of everything.
- Yeah, well, I always do.

01:23:44.347 --> 01:23:46.110
Been great.
Keep in touch.

01:24:24.852 --> 01:24:26.717
You guys remember the sheik.
- Yeah.

01:24:26.787 --> 01:24:28.015
Well, he proposed to me,...

01:24:28.089 --> 01:24:30.455
and I think I loved him,
despite his billions.

01:24:30.524 --> 01:24:32.151
Then why didn't you say "yes"?

01:24:32.226 --> 01:24:34.319
Because I hesitated
long enough to realize...

01:24:34.395 --> 01:24:36.989
my head and my heart were saying
two different things.

01:24:37.064 --> 01:24:38.929
It's this way.
- Yeah.

01:24:39.000 --> 01:24:40.467
Well, it's a big decision.

01:24:40.534 --> 01:24:42.525
Well, it's supposed to be
the easiest one you ever make.

01:24:42.603 --> 01:24:43.797
Wasn't it?

01:24:46.906 --> 01:24:48.373
Hey, Tabby, this is it...

01:24:48.441 --> 01:24:50.932
this is the stuff
I was telling you about.

01:24:51.011 --> 01:24:53.309
"Deep South Glass."

01:24:53.380 --> 01:24:56.144
Oh, yes. Let's.

01:25:22.207 --> 01:25:24.004
What's the matter?

01:25:24.076 --> 01:25:25.236
Oh, my God.

01:25:27.612 --> 01:25:30.843
Do we know...

01:25:30.915 --> 01:25:32.542
Mo'?

01:25:41.759 --> 01:25:43.283
Mel?

01:26:10.052 --> 01:26:12.316
Look at these.

01:26:12.388 --> 01:26:15.255
It's what happens to sand
when it's struck by lightning.

01:26:15.324 --> 01:26:16.916
She's pulling your dick.

01:26:16.992 --> 01:26:19.893
No, really.
I've seen it.

01:26:19.962 --> 01:26:22.055
You just have to dig it up.

01:26:34.175 --> 01:26:35.733
Oh, hey, Bryant.

01:26:35.810 --> 01:26:36.902
Friend of yours?

01:26:51.658 --> 01:26:54.286
I saw him first.

01:26:54.361 --> 01:26:58.320
I, uh...
think he's already taken.

01:27:03.203 --> 01:27:05.296
I tried to call you
a couple of times.

01:27:06.440 --> 01:27:08.340
Listen, since you're here,...

01:27:08.409 --> 01:27:12.095
you and your friends should look
around and have some lunch.

01:27:12.178 --> 01:27:14.305
Y'all should sit
on the deck. It's nice.

01:27:21.921 --> 01:27:26.985
Come on, Bryant, let's, uh...
let's leave this lady alone.

01:27:28.895 --> 01:27:30.361
Come on.

01:27:34.933 --> 01:27:36.093
Come on, boy.

01:27:40.238 --> 01:27:41.830
Yes, sir.
Can we help you?

01:27:42.908 --> 01:27:46.173
I'm... I'm looking
for a Melanie Carmichael.

01:27:47.379 --> 01:27:48.778
Anybody here recognize that name?

01:27:48.847 --> 01:27:50.109
No.

01:27:50.182 --> 01:27:52.615
What business you got with her?

01:27:52.683 --> 01:27:55.015
I'm afraid that's a private matter.

01:27:56.253 --> 01:27:58.517
Well, then, I'm afraid
we can't help you.

01:28:09.733 --> 01:28:11.633
Damn reporters.

01:28:11.701 --> 01:28:14.397
Like the first ant at a picnic.

01:28:16.072 --> 01:28:20.372
Now... this one here's
from Louisiana.

01:28:20.443 --> 01:28:23.105
See? It's got
a little alligator on top.

01:28:23.179 --> 01:28:25.875
How sweet. I can see where
your daughter gets her taste.

01:28:32.921 --> 01:28:35.446
This is one of those disasters
waiting to happen.

01:28:35.524 --> 01:28:38.186
You know, one of the big ones
that only cockroaches survive.

01:28:38.260 --> 01:28:39.693
It's going to be fine.

01:28:51.374 --> 01:28:53.568
One down...
7 million to go.

01:28:53.642 --> 01:28:54.870
Careful.

01:28:54.943 --> 01:28:56.604
You just smashed
the state bird of Alabama.

01:29:01.249 --> 01:29:03.012
Well, finally.
- Hi! How are you?!

01:29:03.084 --> 01:29:04.779
Hey, buddy.
- Hello, sir.

01:29:04.853 --> 01:29:07.253
Well, I can see
why Melanie is so adorable.

01:29:07.322 --> 01:29:08.689
I'm so happy to be here.

01:29:11.193 --> 01:29:13.252
We're so happy
to have you here.

01:29:13.328 --> 01:29:15.192
I'm sorry the place is
such a mess, Mrs. Hennings...

01:29:15.262 --> 01:29:16.229
Mayor... ma'am!

01:29:16.297 --> 01:29:18.356
No, no, no, no, no...
don't you dare. It's "Kate."

01:29:18.432 --> 01:29:20.195
You know, I've been
tryin' to get Earl...

01:29:20.267 --> 01:29:23.134
to weed these shrubberies
and repaint the trim.

01:29:23.204 --> 01:29:27.436
And... oh, my God,
look how pretty she is, Earl.

01:29:27.508 --> 01:29:29.874
Yeah, I'll bet Kate
could use a drink.

01:29:29.977 --> 01:29:31.638
Kate could, indeed.

01:29:31.812 --> 01:29:33.475
Well, just come right on in.

01:29:33.547 --> 01:29:37.704
I've got some fried pickles,
hot right out of the grease.

01:29:37.984 --> 01:29:41.010
Had a lot of trouble
getting my house painted, too.

01:29:42.589 --> 01:29:44.648
It's a lovely chair, Earl.

01:29:44.724 --> 01:29:47.916
Yeah, but to get the full effect,
you got to pull this here handle.

01:29:48.027 --> 01:29:49.551
Daddy, no!

01:29:49.629 --> 01:29:51.790
Now, you hold onto
your drink, Kate, and watch.

01:29:56.101 --> 01:29:58.433
We're so sorry, Kate!
- We'll get you up.

01:30:17.488 --> 01:30:19.183
Name?

01:30:19.257 --> 01:30:21.020
Uh, Buford...
Wallace Buford.

01:30:21.092 --> 01:30:22.582
I'm not on that list,

01:30:22.660 --> 01:30:25.026
but I've got some urgent
business with the bride.

01:30:25.096 --> 01:30:27.792
Not today, you don't.
Trooper?

01:30:27.865 --> 01:30:29.799
All right, sir, let's get it
turned around here.

01:30:56.993 --> 01:30:59.754
Hey, there's a weddin' goin' on.

01:30:59.828 --> 01:31:02.126
Yeah, I heard mention of it
a time or two.

01:31:02.197 --> 01:31:05.792
I sure hope this weather cooperates.

01:31:05.868 --> 01:31:08.769
It's supposed to be a big one.

01:31:08.837 --> 01:31:10.304
You know, Jake...

01:31:11.740 --> 01:31:18.008
You're my only son...
and I love you, but sometimes...

01:31:18.346 --> 01:31:23.249
you are too much
like your daddy.

01:31:23.318 --> 01:31:25.843
She made her decision, Mama.

01:31:28.089 --> 01:31:31.718
For somebody who's been holdin'
onto somethin' so hard,...

01:31:31.793 --> 01:31:33.658
you're pretty quick
to let it go.

01:31:36.964 --> 01:31:41.160
You know, I can't control her any
more than I can control the weather.

01:31:54.348 --> 01:31:56.043
It's just nerves.

01:31:56.116 --> 01:31:58.516
You're doin' the right thing.

01:31:59.618 --> 01:32:01.142
Am I?

01:32:03.122 --> 01:32:05.750
When I married your daddy...

01:32:05.825 --> 01:32:08.919
oh, Lord, but I was
a fool for that man.

01:32:08.994 --> 01:32:11.519
I couldn't put one foot
in front of the other.

01:32:11.597 --> 01:32:13.622
I remember standin' there,
thinkin',...

01:32:13.699 --> 01:32:17.897
"Oh, preacher, hurry up
before he changes his mind."

01:32:18.370 --> 01:32:20.233
Look where it got me.

01:32:21.506 --> 01:32:25.931
Sometimes that man makes me so mad,
I could just wring his neck.

01:32:26.044 --> 01:32:27.534
But you still love him.

01:32:27.612 --> 01:32:29.102
God knows I do.

01:32:30.180 --> 01:32:32.547
And only he knows why.

01:32:32.617 --> 01:32:34.482
Mama... I think I...

01:32:34.552 --> 01:32:39.353
He can give you a life
that we never dreamed of.

01:32:39.424 --> 01:32:41.254
And he adores you.

01:32:45.462 --> 01:32:46.952
He does, doesn't he?

01:33:20.997 --> 01:33:24.693
Well, even if he is a Yankee,
at least he's sober.

01:33:24.766 --> 01:33:25.926
Ms. Carmichael!

01:33:26.001 --> 01:33:27.696
Hey!
- Ms. Carmichael!

01:33:27.769 --> 01:33:29.669
Get him!
- Ms. Carmichael!

01:33:29.738 --> 01:33:30.727
Get back here!

01:33:36.711 --> 01:33:38.269
Mr. Buford?

01:33:38.646 --> 01:33:40.712
Get your hands off me!

01:33:40.782 --> 01:33:42.476
Wait! Let him go.

01:33:46.353 --> 01:33:47.718
Melanie?

01:33:47.888 --> 01:33:51.083
You are one hard woman
to get in touch with.

01:33:52.860 --> 01:33:55.761
Mr. Buford, he signed the papers.

01:33:55.830 --> 01:33:57.320
What are you doing here?

01:34:02.736 --> 01:34:06.330
He did... you didn't.

01:34:07.540 --> 01:34:09.565
What?

01:34:14.547 --> 01:34:16.208
You mean I'm still married?

01:34:18.117 --> 01:34:20.881
Well, not unless you want to be.

01:34:20.954 --> 01:34:22.649
Oh, for God's sakes, Melanie.

01:34:22.722 --> 01:34:24.586
I thought you took care of this.

01:34:24.656 --> 01:34:26.317
It's an honest mistake, Andrew.

01:34:26.391 --> 01:34:28.985
Well, then, can we fix it
before we all get soaked?

01:34:29.061 --> 01:34:31.154
Does anybody have a pen?

01:34:34.299 --> 01:34:36.392
Mom?
- Oh, yeah, sure.

01:34:36.468 --> 01:34:38.402
Go on, check your purse.

01:34:42.407 --> 01:34:44.738
These things don't
just happen, you know.

01:34:47.078 --> 01:34:50.047
Can't ride two horses
with one ass, sugar bean.

01:35:25.348 --> 01:35:26.439
Andrew...

01:35:28.150 --> 01:35:29.811
You don't want to marry me.

01:35:29.885 --> 01:35:32.914
